.TH "ccio_map_single" 9 "ccio_map_single" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
ccio_map_single \- Map an address range into the IOMMU.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "dma_addr_t" ccio_map_single
.BI "(struct device *dev "  ","
.BI "void *addr "  ","
.BI "size_t size "  ","
.BI "enum dma_data_direction direction "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "dev" 12
The PCI device.
.IP "addr" 12
The start address of the DMA region.
.IP "size" 12
The length of the DMA region.
.IP "direction" 12
The direction of the DMA transaction (to/from device).
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
This function implements the pci_map_single function.
